DE ISSUES IN TELECOMMUNICATIONS AND INFORMATION. VOLUME IV. THE ROLE OF THEUNITED STATES GOVERNMENT IN THE FINANCING OF EXPORTS OF MAJORTELECOMMUNICATIONS AND INFORMATION PRODUCTS.     EXAMINES THE ROLE WHICH THE USA PLAYS IN THE FINANCING OF EXPORTS OF MAJORTELECOMMUNICATIONS AND INFORMATION PRODUCTS. THIS ROLE IS PRINCIPALLYPERFORMED BY 3 GOVERNMENT AGENCIES' THE EXPORT-IMPORT BANK, THE AGENCY FORINTERNATIONAL DEVELOPMENT, AND THE TRADE AND DEVELOPMENT PROGRAM. AQUANTITATIVE REVIEW OF THE PRESENT AND PAST ACTIVITIES OF THESE 3 AGENCIES INTHE TELECOMMUNICATIONS AND INFORMATION SECTOR IS PROVIDED, FOLLOWED BY ANEXAMINATION OF THE INSTITUTIONAL AND FUNDING CONSTRAINTS WHICH SERVE TO LIMITTHESE ACTIVITIES. FINALLY, THE POTENTIAL FUTURE ROLE OF EACH OF THESE AGENCIESIN THIS SECTOR IS DISCUSSED